<div class="question"><li>
So you are just another Translation Memory?
</li></div>
<div class="answer">No. Strictly speaking, TraduXio is not a Translation Memory. 
Whereas traditional Translation Memory devices are limited to two languages (source/target), Traduxio allows the comparison between many different versions of the same text. 
Moreover, for TraduXio offers a (social) tagging/classification system of the source-text (according to its literary genre, author, historical period, etc.), it enables a better management of translated texts.
</div>
