</li></div>
<div class="answer">
TraduXio respects copyright (and “droit d’auteur”) regulations. The site contains only works taken from the public domain. Translations of protected texts are possible but require previous authorization from copyright holders.
TraduXio would like to value the work of translators and their rights, while promoting a spirit of mutualisation, through the use of open licenses. 
</div>
</div>


